  {
    "user": "U06MJU6LBN3",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1732628882.139409",
    "edited": {
      "user": "U06MJU6LBN3",
      "ts": "1732630586.000000"
    },
    "client_msg_id": "416e90af-9436-4e03-baf4-b41b5bd23614",
    "text": "Hey, I'm working on <https://www.smallweb.run/|smallweb>, a self-hostable personal cloud.\n\nIt's inspired by by serveless platforms like val.town and old standards like cgi-bin. I still struggle to describe it. It feels like coding in dropbox, but in a good way.\n\nFor example, if I want to host my new blog in smallweb, I can do it by just creating a new folder at `~/smallweb/blog/main.ts` :\n\n```import { Smallblog } from \"jsr:@tayzendev/smallblog@1.1.5\";\n\nexport default new Smallblog({\n  siteTitle: \"Pomdtr's Blog\",\n  defaultAuthors: [\"pomdtr\"],\n});\n```\nThen, no need to run any terminal command or to wait for a deploy step, my blog is instantly available on the `<http://blog.pomdtr.me|blog.pomdtr.me>` subdomain: <https://blog.pomdtr.me|https://blog.pomdtr.me> (this one is hosted on my raspberrypi).\n\nApps also have write access to their own dir. For example, if you go to <https://vscode-demo.smallweb.run|https://vscode-demo.smallweb.run>, you'll be able to write in my own smallweb dir. Or feel free to draw me something at <https://excalidraw.smallweb.run|https://excalidraw.smallweb.run> !\n\nAll of the websites hosted under the `smallweb.run` domain are open-source, and can be found at: <https://gh.smallweb.run|https://gh.smallweb.run>",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "qDsJZ",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Hey, I'm working on "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://www.smallweb.run/",
                "text": "smallweb"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", a self-hostable personal cloud.\n\nIt's inspired by by serveless platforms like val.town and old standards like cgi-bin. I still struggle to describe it. It feels like coding in dropbox, but in a good way.\n\nFor example, if I want to host my new blog in smallweb, I can do it by just creating a new folder at "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "~/smallweb/blog/main.ts",
                "style": {
                  "code": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " :\n\n"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "import { Smallblog } from \"jsr:@tayzendev/smallblog@1.1.5\";\n\nexport default new Smallblog({\n  siteTitle: \"Pomdtr's Blog\",\n  defaultAuthors: [\"pomdtr\"],\n});\n"
              }
            ],
            "border": 0
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\nThen, no need to run any terminal command or to wait for a deploy step, my blog is instantly available on the "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "http://blog.pomdtr.me",
                "text": "blog.pomdtr.me",
                "style": {
                  "code": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " subdomain: "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://blog.pomdtr.me",
                "text": "https://blog.pomdtr.me"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " (this one is hosted on my raspberrypi).\n\nApps also have write access to their own dir. For example, if you go to "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://vscode-demo.smallweb.run",
                "text": "https://vscode-demo.smallweb.run"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", you'll be able to write in my own smallweb dir. Or feel free to draw me something at "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://excalidraw.smallweb.run",
                "text": "https://excalidraw.smallweb.run"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " !\n\nAll of the websites hosted under the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "smallweb.run",
                "style": {
                  "code": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " domain are open-source, and can be found at: "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://gh.smallweb.run",
                "text": "https://gh.smallweb.run"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
